patch.comment: Bump minimatch from 10.1.2 to 10.2.1

Add `"node"` condition before `"import"` in the `"exports"` map so that Node.js uses the CJS output (which handles extensionless imports), while bundlers still use ESM via `"import"`. Fixes https://github.com/microsoft/rushstack/issues/5644.
Fix an issue where `lib-` folders were excluded from publish.

minor.comment: Normalize package layout. CommonJS is now under `lib-commonjs`, DTS is now under `lib-dts`, and ESM is now under `lib-esm`. Imports to `lib` still work as before, handled by the `"exports"` field in `package.json`.

patch.comment: Update minimatch dependency from 10.0.3 to 10.1.2
Upgrade npm-packlist from ~2.1.2 to ~5.1.3 to remove deprecated glob@7 and inflight dependencies

minor.comment: Normalize import of builtin modules to use the `node:` protocol.

patch.comment: Upgrades the minimatch dependency from ~3.0.3 to 10.0.3 across the entire Rush monorepo to address a Regular Expression Denial of Service (ReDoS) vulnerability in the underlying brace-expansion dependency.
Prefer `os.availableParallelism()` to `os.cpus().length`.

minor.comment: Add bin linking support when calling the create-links.js script with the "--link-bins" parameter

patch.comment: Fix an issue where the `node_modules/.bin` folder symlinks were not created for extracted packages when using the "default" link creation mode

minor.comment: Add a `files` field to the `extractor-metadata.json` file
Add the ability to change where the "create-links.js" file and the associated metadata file are generated when running in the "script" linkCreation mode

patch.comment: Include CHANGELOG.md in published releases again
Fix broken link to API documentation
Fix an issue with the `folderToCopy` option, where the folder contents would be copied into a subfolder instead of into the target folder root.
Links that target a path outside of the source directory can now be ignored using "patternsToInclude" and "patternsToExclude" options
Fix line endings in published package.
Ensure the "folderToCopy" field is included in generated archives
Update type-only imports to include the type modifier.
Fix an issue where subdirectory inclusion patterns (ex. "src/subdir/**/*") would get ignored during extraction

minor.comment: Add option field dependenciesConfigurations in PackageExtractor to filter files for third party dependencies
Include an API for getting files that are included in a npm package.

patch.comment: Fix patternsToInclude and patternsToExclude filters when provided patterns target subdirectories of folders that do not match the provided patterns

minor.comment: Allow for include and exclude filters to be provided for projects. This allows for an additional layer of filtering when extracting a package.

patch.comment: Bump webpack to v5.82.1
Export typings for the extractor-metadata.json file

minor.comment: Bundle the `create-links` script to ensure any imports that are added in the future don't cause issues.

patch.comment: Fix typings reference in package.json

minor.comment: Create new @rushstack/package-extractor package allowing for deployment of a target package and associated dependencies
